---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

/*Imports a component, leadershipbox and mentorbox. So styling is a bit easier, as each one connects back to the component*/
import LeadershipBox from '../components/LeadershipBox.astro';
import MentorBox from '../components/MentorBox.astro';

---
<Layout>
	<!-- Wrapper for department section -->
	<div class="py-5 bg-lm-dark-gray dark:bg-dm-highlight-gray">

		<!-- Title -->
		<div class="py-5 md:py-8 max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
			<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-lm-text dark:text-dm-text font-mono mb-6">Our Team - Departments</h1>
		</div>
	
		<!-- Engineering Section -->
		<section class="py-6 md:py-8">
	
			<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
				<h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium text-lm-text dark:text-dm-text font-mono mb-6">
					Engineering Department
				</h2>
	
				<!-- Description -->
				<p class="text-lm-text-muted-alt dark:text-dm-text-muted text-lg max-w-4xl leading-relaxed">
					The engineering department is composed of two separate sub-teams which work together to design and build the robot. 
					Before the build season, both sub-teams hold curriculum meetings to teach newer members how to operate workshop tools 
					and use CAD programs. In addition, they teach basic design processes so everyone can help with the final design. 
					Throughout the build season, the engineering department is responsible for designing and building the robot within the 
					timeframe. During competition, department members are the primary group in the pit, so they can fix any problems that may 
					arise. 
				</p>
			</div>
	
			<!-- Image  -->
			<div class="py-10 max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
				<img 
					src="/assets/Department Photos/EngineeringImage.JPG" 
					alt="Iron Riders Engineering Photo 2025" 
					class="w-[40vh] h-[40vh] md:w-[50vh] md:h-[50vh] object-cover object-top p-4 bg-lm-highlight-gray dark:bg-dm-light-gray"
				/>
			</div>
		</section>
	
		<!-- Software Section -->
		<section class="py-6 md:py-8">
	
			<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
				<h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium text-lm-text dark:text-dm-text font-mono mb-6">
					Software Department
				</h2>
	
				<!-- Description -->
				<p class="text-lm-text-muted-alt dark:text-dm-text-muted text-lg max-w-4xl leading-relaxed">
					The Software Department is responsible for the backend of the robot. Before the build season, they teach newer members 
					how to use Java and the tools they use to code, such as VSCode. During the build season, they write the code for the robot,
					including not only basic driving and manipulator control, but also image recognition, motion profiling, and more. They test
					the robot rigorously to ensure everything works as expected, which is then handed off to Drive Team. 
				</p>
			</div>
	
			<!-- Image  -->
			<div class="py-10 max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
				<img 
					src="/assets/Department Photos/SoftwareImage.JPG" 
					alt="Iron Riders Software Photo 2025" 
					class="w-[40vh] h-[40vh] md:w-[50vh] md:h-[50vh] object-cover object-top p-4 bg-lm-highlight-gray dark:bg-dm-light-gray"
				/>
			</div>
		</section>
	
		<!-- Business Section -->
		<section class="flex-col py-6 md:py-8">
	
			<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
				<h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium text-lm-text dark:text-dm-text font-mono mb-6">
					Business Department
				</h2>
	
				<!-- Description -->
				<p class="text-lm-text-muted-alt dark:text-dm-text-muted text-lg max-w-4xl leading-relaxed">
					The business department has a wide range of responsibilities throughout the year. At the start of the year, the Business 
					Department focuses on finding sponsors and applying for available grants to obtain team funds. Throughout the build season,
					the department handles money and purchase requests for the various components required. In addition to these, the department 
					has a variety of other tasks, such as logo voting, working with communications, and team branding. 
				</p>
			</div>
	
			<!-- Image  -->
			<div class="py-10 max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
				<img 
					src="/assets/Department Photos/Finance.JPG" 
					alt="Iron Riders Strategy Placeholder Photo 2025" 
					class="w-[40vh] h-[40vh] md:w-[50vh] md:h-[50vh] object-cover object-top p-4 bg-lm-highlight-gray dark:bg-dm-light-gray"
				/>
			</div>
		</section>
	
		<!-- Strategy Section -->
		<section class="py-6 md:py-8">
	
			<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
				<h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-medium text-lm-text dark:text-dm-text font-mono mb-6">
					Strategy Department
				</h2>
	
				<!-- Description -->
				<p class="text-lm-text-muted-alt dark:text-dm-text-muted text-lg max-w-4xl leading-relaxed">
					The Strategy Department is responsible for having expertise in the rules and regulations of the game. This includes 
					determining how the robot will play, piloting the robot during the teleoperated period, and strategizing with other 
					teams on our alliance. 
				</p>
			</div>
	
			<!-- Image  -->
			<div class="py-10 max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
				<img 
					src="/assets/Department Photos/StrategyImage.JPG" 
					alt="Iron Riders Finance Placeholder Photo 2025" 
					class="w-[40vh] h-[40vh] md:w-[50vh] md:h-[50vh] object-cover object-top p-4 bg-lm-highlight-gray dark:bg-dm-light-gray"
				/>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>

	<!-- Wrapper for leadership section -->
	<div class="py-10 bg-lm-dark-gray dark:bg-dm-light-gray">
		
		<!-- Title + Desc -->
		<div class="py-5 md:py-8 max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
			<!-- Title -->
			<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-lm-text dark:text-dm-text font-mono mb-6">Our Team - Leadership</h1>

			<!-- Desc -->
			<p class="text-lm-text-muted-alt dark:text-dm-text-muted text-lg max-w-4xl leading-relaxed">
				Big shoutout to all of our incredible student leaders who spend countless hours to our team! 
			</p>
		</div>

		
	
		<!-- Flex-col of leadership! -->
		<div class="flex-col flex gap-10 justify-center py-15">
			<!-- Top leadership -->
			<div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row justify-center items-center lg:space-x-30">
				<LeadershipBox
					person="Anna Lai";
					title="Operations Executive";
					image="../assets/Leadership photos/COO.JPG"
				/>

				<LeadershipBox
					person="Kaylee Shin";
					title="Technical Executive";
					image="../assets/Leadership photos/CTO.JPG"
				/>				
			</div>

			<!-- Secondary leadership P1-->
			<div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row justify-center items-center lg:space-x-30">
				<LeadershipBox
					person="Andrew Day";
					title="Build Director";
					image="../assets/Leadership photos/Build Director.JPG"
				/>

				<LeadershipBox
					person="William Wagner";
					title="Design Director";
					image="../assets/Leadership photos/Design Director.JPG"
				/>	

				<LeadershipBox
					person="Ryan Elbert";
					title="Controls Director";
					image="../assets/Leadership photos/Software Director.JPG"
				/>			
			</div>
			<!-- Secondary leadership P2-->
			<div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row justify-center items-center lg:space-x-30">
				<LeadershipBox
					person="Lynn Anderson";
					title="Communications Director";
					image="../assets/Leadership photos/Communications Director.JPG"
				/>

				<LeadershipBox
					person="Kira Outhred";
					title="Strategy Director";
					image="../assets/Leadership photos/Strategy Director.JPG"
				/>	

				<LeadershipBox
					person="Lalitha Muralidhar";
					title="Finance Director";
					image="../assets/Leadership photos/Finance Director.JPG"
				/>			
			</div>
			<!-- Secondary leadership P3-->
			<div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row justify-center items-center lg:space-x-30">
				<LeadershipBox
					person="Rio Johnson";
					title="Marketing Director";
					image="../assets/Leadership photos/Marketing Director.JPG"
				/>

				<LeadershipBox
					person="Zoe Bates";
					title="Outreach Director";
					image="../assets/Leadership photos/Outreach Director.JPG"
				/>	
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<!-- Wrapper for leadership section -->
	<div class="py-10 bg-lm-dark-gray dark:bg-dm-highlight-gray">
		
		<!-- Title + Desc -->
		<div class="py-5 md:py-8 max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
			<!-- Title -->
			<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-lm-text dark:text-dm-text font-mono mb-6">Our Team - Mentors</h1>

			<!-- Desc -->
			<p class="text-lm-text-muted-alt dark:text-dm-text-muted text-lg max-w-4xl leading-relaxed">
				The following is a list of all of our incredible mentors who help us throughout the year!
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Flex-col of mentors! -->
		<div class="flex-col flex gap-10 justify-center py-15">

			<!-- head mentor P1 -->
			<div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row justify-center items-center lg:space-x-30">
				<MentorBox
					person="John Luetke";
					title="Team Coach";
					image="../assets/logo.png";
				/>
				
			</div>

			<!-- mentors P2-->
			<div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row justify-center items-center lg:space-x-30">
				<MentorBox
					person="James Gladden";
					title="Engineering Mentor";
					image="../assets/logo.png";
				/>

				<MentorBox
